dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Northern provinces of the Kingdom of Fas are listed. Includes inset map: City of Marocco (Marraksh Blad Kibira); city gates and mosques are listed and located. Includes elevation profile: "Section of the Empire of Marocco, in a North and South Direction in Long[itu]de 7°30' W. nearly". From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 1, (1830-31), p. 123-55; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.1 1830-31
dc_publisher_s: London : [published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society by John Murray, Albemarle Street], 1831.
